---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: '10Web AI',
    slug: '/reviews/10web'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Relume AI',
    slug: '/reviews/relume'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    tenweb: 'Best for building complete WordPress sites',
    relume: 'Best for planning site structure before building',
    winner: 'They complement each other. Use Relume to plan, 10Web to build.'
};

---

<Layout title="10Web AI vs Relume AI: Planning vs Building">

  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: '10Web AI vs Relume AI: Planning vs Building',
      description: '10Web builds WordPress sites with AI. Relume AI generates sitemaps and wireframes for planning. They\'re not competitors—they\'re workflow partners. Here\'s how to use them together.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/10web-vs-relume'
    }}
  />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">10Web AI vs Relume AI:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Planning vs Building</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Relume generates sitemaps and wireframes—it's a planning tool, not a builder. 10Web builds actual WordPress sites with AI. They're not competitors. They're complementary tools for different stages of the workflow.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Relume to plan your site structure (sitemap, wireframes).<br />
            Use 10Web to actually build it in WordPress.<br /><br />
            Relume is the architect. 10Web is the builder. They work together.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume generates sitemaps and wireframes. It doesn't build actual websites. You export to Webflow, Figma, or Framer and build from there. It's for planning—structuring content, defining pages, creating wireframes before you build.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web generates complete WordPress sites. You enter prompts, it builds actual pages with content, images, styling. It's for building—creating the final website live on WordPress with hosting, CMS, e-commerce.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">10Web AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.tenweb}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Relume AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.relume}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">10Web AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Relume AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">What it builds</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Complete WordPress site</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Sitemaps & wireframes</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Different tools</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Output</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Live WordPress site</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Export to Webflow/Figma</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Different tools</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">E-commerce</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WooCommerce</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Wireframes only</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Use case</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Building live sites</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Planning site structure</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Different tools</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Export options</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WordPress</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Webflow, Figma, Framer</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Different tools</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$10-60</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Contact sales</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where 10Web wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Complete websites</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web builds actual live websites with hosting, CMS, analytics, e-commerce. Relume creates wireframes and sitemaps—you still need to build the actual site. If you want a finished website, 10Web is the only option here.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">WordPress ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web gives you WordPress—60,000 plugins, any theme, any developer can help. Relume exports to Webflow/Framer which are proprietary ecosystems. For long-term flexibility, 10Web wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web has full WooCommerce integration. Relume can wireframe an e-commerce site but you'll need to build it in Webflow or another platform. For actual online stores, 10Web is the practical choice.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Relume wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Planning phase</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Before building, you need to plan. Relume generates complete sitemaps with page hierarchies, content structure, wireframes. It's invaluable for complex sites with many pages. 10Web doesn't do planning.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Client presentations</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Relume wireframes are perfect for client presentations—show structure without committing to design. 10Web generates finished sites which can make clients hesitant to suggest changes.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Webflow integration</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If you build in Webflow, Relume is the perfect planning tool. Export sitemap and wireframes directly to Webflow, then build. 10Web is WordPress-only, so if Webflow is your target, Relume wins.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>My Experience
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          A SaaS startup needed a 45-page marketing site with complex information architecture. Product pages, pricing tiers, documentation, blog, careers, integrations, case studies. They were debating between 10Web (WordPress) and Relume (planning).
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Relume-first approach</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Started with Relume AI. Generated complete sitemap in 4 minutes—48 pages including pages the client forgot (press, API docs, partner program, careers). Spent 2 hours reviewing sitemap with stakeholders. Found 4 missing pages during planning. Restructured based on feedback. Exported wireframes as PDF for approval. Then imported structure into 10Web and built WordPress site. Total time: 3 weeks. Zero restructures needed.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The 10Web-direct approach</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Started building in 10Web directly with AI generation. Generated 12 initial pages. Built out to 28 pages over 3 weeks. Client review: "User flow is wrong. Can't find documentation. Missing case studies. Careers page is buried." Spent 1 week restructuring—deleting pages, reorganizing content, fixing navigation. Another week updating redesigned pages. Total time: 5 weeks. Everyone exhausted.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/10 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The brutal truth:</strong> 2 hours of Relume planning saved 2 weeks of rework.<br /><br />
            <strong>The workflow:</strong> Relume for sitemap planning → 10Web for WordPress building. They're complementary, not competitors.<br /><br />
            <strong>The ROI:</strong> At founder's €150/hour opportunity cost, that's €12,000 in savings. Plus, site launched 2 weeks earlier—generating revenue sooner.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>The flip side:</strong> A simple 8-page restaurant website. Menu, location, reservations, about. No complex information architecture.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">With Relume + 10Web:</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Generated sitemap in Relume (3 minutes). Reviewed with client (15 minutes). Approved structure. Built in 10Web (2 days). Total time: 3 days including planning.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">10Web only:</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Generated site directly in 10Web (2 minutes). Built out pages (2 days). Minor tweaks to navigation (30 minutes). Total time: 2.5 days.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-gray-500 p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-medium">
            <strong>The lesson:</strong> Relume saves proportional to complexity. For simple sites (5-10 pages), you can skip planning. For complex sites (20+ pages), Relume planning prevents weeks of rework.<br /><br />
            Use Relume when information architecture matters. Skip it for simple brochure sites. 10Web handles both—Relume just helps you plan the complex ones.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>How to use them together
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The smartest workflow: Use Relume first, 10Web second.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 1: Plan with Relume</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Generate sitemap for your site. Review page structure. Export wireframes. Get client approval on structure before building.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Step 2: Build with 10Web</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Use the Relume sitemap as your blueprint. Generate pages in 10Web following the planned structure. Build live WordPress site from the plan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web and Relume aren't competitors—they're workflow partners. Relume is for planning (sitemap, wireframes). 10Web is for building (WordPress site, hosting, CMS).<br /><br />
          If you're building a complex site, use Relume to plan first, then 10Web to build. For simple sites, just use 10Web directly. If you're a Webflow user, use Relume to plan, then build in Webflow instead of 10Web.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read 10Web review
          </a>
          <a href={comparisonData.tool2.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Relume review
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

</Layout>
